    <!-- 60/40 Layout: Content + Sidebar -->
    <section class="program-shell program-shell--6040">
      <div class="program-content">

        <!-- OVERVIEW -->
        <section class="program-section">
          <h2>Overview</h2>
          <p>
            The Sports Path helps participants build confidence, relationships, and leadership through sports.
            Some participants engage by playing; others thrive in support roles that keep them close to the team.
            We meet people where they are — and help them grow over time.
          </p>

          <h3>Core components</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Community-based sports (including Challenger and recreational programs)</li>
            <li>Fitness and movement routines that reinforce confidence and wellness</li>
            <li>Team belonging through game-day routines and social connection</li>
            <li>Optional sports media/storytelling (highlights, interviews, commentary)</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- CONTINUUM (NEW) -->
        <section class="program-section" id="continuum">
          <h2>A Lifelong Sports Participation Continuum</h2>
          <p>
            Every participant’s sports journey is different — and it can evolve. This pathway supports a
            progression from entry-level engagement to meaningful team contribution and leadership.
          </p>

          <h3>Phase 1: Engage</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Try sports in supportive settings</li>
            <li>Build comfort with routines, rules, and environments</li>
            <li>Strengthen social connection through team culture</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Phase 2: Contribute</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Step into structured, reliable roles on a team</li>
            <li>Build responsibility through checklists and repeatable tasks</li>
            <li>Support game-day operations and team readiness</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Phase 3: Lead</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Mentor younger participants</li>
            <li>Represent community pride and inclusive team identity</li>
            <li>Grow visibility through sports storytelling and leadership</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- SCHOOL TEAM SUPPORT ROLES (NEW) -->
        <section class="program-section" id="for-schools">
          <h2>School Team Support Roles</h2>
          <p>
            Many participants form deep, positive relationships with school athletic communities.
            When they age out, those connections can be interrupted due to administrative and liability concerns.
            We help schools keep what’s working by providing a structured, supervised framework for inclusion.
          </p>

          <h3>Example roles</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Team Manager Assistant</strong> (equipment, checklists, setup, breakdown)</li>
            <li><strong>Game-Day Operations</strong> (water, supplies, sideline readiness)</li>
            <li><strong>Stats / Film / Media Assistant</strong> (filming, simple stat tracking, highlights)</li>
            <li><strong>Team Culture Ambassador</strong> (morale, pre-game routines, introductions)</li>
            <li><strong>Community Storytelling Crew</strong> (interviews, recaps, social posts)</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Safety & clarity (boundaries)</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>No coaching or instruction</li>
            <li>No independent supervision of minors</li>
            <li>No transporting students</li>
            <li>On-site supervision by a designated staff member</li>
            <li>Roles and schedules defined and approved in advance</li>
          </ul>

          <div class="accordion-stack" style="margin-top: 1rem;">
            <details class="accordion">
              <summary>Why schools partner with us</summary>
              <div class="accordion-body">
                <ul>
                  <li>Strengthens team culture through belonging and inclusion</li>
                  <li>Preserves alumni continuity and community pride</li>
                  <li>Provides clear role definitions and boundaries</li>
                  <li>Keeps administrative burden low with ready-made program materials</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </details>

            <details class="accordion">
              <summary>Partnership options (simple → structured)</summary>
              <div class="accordion-body">
                <p>
                  Schools may implement this in multiple ways depending on district preferences:
                </p>
                <ul>
                  <li><strong>Volunteer-aligned model:</strong> participant is approved under district volunteer procedures with a defined role.</li>
                  <li><strong>Nonprofit placement model:</strong> participant is placed through Who’s to Say? with defined supervision and program documentation.</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </details>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- INCLUSION SUPPORT (NEW) -->
        <section class="program-section" id="inclusion">
          <h2>How We Support Inclusive Participation</h2>
          <p>
            Inclusion isn’t just access — it’s intentional support. We collaborate with families, coaches, and partners
            to align roles to strengths, build predictable routines, and support success for everyone involved.
          </p>

          <ul>
            <li><strong>Role matching:</strong> align interests, strengths, and goals to meaningful responsibilities</li>
            <li><strong>Preparation:</strong> checklists, visual prompts, and repeatable routines</li>
            <li><strong>Coach-friendly structure:</strong> clear expectations and boundaries</li>
            <li><strong>Consistency:</strong> light-touch coordination so the experience stays stable</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- OUTCOMES (REFINED) -->
        <section class="program-section" id="outcomes">
          <h2>Outcomes & Skills</h2>
          <p>
            The Sports Path builds transferable life skills through teamwork and responsibility.
          </p>

          <h3>Confidence & belonging</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Team identity, routines, and community presence</li>
            <li>Social comfort in group settings</li>
            <li>Reduced isolation after aging out of school</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Responsibility</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Time-on-task and follow-through</li>
            <li>Operational reliability through repeatable roles</li>
            <li>Ownership and pride in contribution</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Communication & leadership</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Team communication and social fluency</li>
            <li>Storytelling, interviews, commentary (optional)</li>
            <li>Mentoring and inclusive leadership modeling</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- IMPACT STORIES (NEW, SAFE PLACEHOLDER) -->
        <section class="program-section" id="stories">
          <h2>Impact Stories</h2>
          <p>
            We collect stories and reflections from coaches, athletes, families, and participants. As pilots expand,
            we’ll feature real quotes and short profiles here.
          </p>

          <div class="accordion-stack" style="margin-top: 1rem;">
            <details class="accordion">
              <summary>Coach perspective (example)</summary>
              <div class="accordion-body">
                <p>
                  “Having him with our program made the team better — not just as athletes, but as people.”
                </p>
              </div>
            </details>

            <details class="accordion">
              <summary>Family perspective (example)</summary>
              <div class="accordion-body">
                <p>
                  “He feels like he belongs again. The routine and the team gave him purpose.”
                </p>
              </div>
            </details>

            <details class="accordion">
              <summary>Student-athlete perspective (example)</summary>
              <div class="accordion-body">
                <p>
                  “He’s part of our culture. He lifts everyone up.”
                </p>
              </div>
            </details>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- GET STARTED -->
        <section class="program-section" id="get-started">
          <h2>Get Started</h2>
          <p>
            Whether you’re a family, coach, or school leader — we’ll help map a realistic, supportive way to build
            belonging through sports.
          </p>

          <div class="btn-row">
            <a class="btn btn-primary" href="mailto:info@whostosay.org?subject=Sports%20Path%20Inquiry">Email Us</a>
